title: BN+ Brute force hash attacker.rar
description:
BN+ Brute force hash attacker is an easy to use tool to preform brute force attacks on hashes. MD5, RIPEMD160, SHA1, and SHA2 family hashes are supported. Ideal for password recovery, and sending and decoding hash messages. Hashes are text containing data encrypted in an irreversible algorithm, and are most used for storing passwords. More information about hashes can be found in this wikipedia article. If you are looking for a tool to hash text, go to this topic. 

Release date: 2008-11-16
Known issues:None

Program version: 1.0.5
Front end language: English
System requirements
> Win 2000 / Win Xp / Win Vista
> .Net framework 2.0 or higher 

Developer: De Dauw Jeroen
Written in: Visual Basic.net and visual C# .Net, using Visual Studio 2008
